Class Level

java.lang.Object
sample.start.Level
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<GameObject>
public final class Level
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<GameObject>
Level saved a level using 3 different GameGrid objects and provide several methods related to position.

  • Constructor Details

    • Level

      public Level​(java.lang.String levelName, int levelIndex, java.util.List<java.lang.String> raw_level)
      This is the only constructor of the Level class. It saves a level using 3 different GameGrid objects. It saves a objectsGrid which saves everything except diamonds. It saves a diamondsGrid which only saves diamonds. It also saves a allObjectsGrid which is same as objectsGrid for further use.
      Parameters:
      levelName - String representing the level name.
      levelIndex - int representing the level index.
      raw_level - List<String> contains String of GameObject.
